SEC. 18. Section 25 of Republic Act No. 10068 is hereby amended and renumbered, to read as follows:

"SEC. 26.

Appropriations.

x x x.

The Department of Budget and Management shall include annually in the President's program of expenditure for submission to and approval by Congress One billion pesos (P1,000,000,000.00) for the promotion and development of the national Organic Agriculture Program, allocated as follows:

Thirty-five percent (35%) for shared facilities;

Twenty-five percent (25%) for seeds development/planting materials and animals distribution and feed for aquaculture, soil amendments and bio-control agents;

Twenty percent (20%) for extension and training;

Five percent (5%) for socialized credit;

Five percent (5%) for small scale irrigation system;

Five percent (5%) for research and development;

and

Five percent (5%) for marketing and promotion.

